  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" Singamasetty Bhagavath Guptha & Anr. versus Allam Karibasappa (D) by Lrs./Allam Doddabasappa (D) by Lrs. & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_9_1539_1558','2025INSC1159'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SINGAMASETTY BHAGAVATH GUPTHA & ANR.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>ALLAM KARIBASAPPA (D) BY LRS./ALLAM DODDABASAPPA (D) BY LRS. & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 9 S.C.R. 1539</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1159</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008982025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PAMIDIGHANTAM SRI NARASIMHA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether in the facts and circumstances of the case, the High Court erred in holding that all the acts done by the official receiver between the declaration of the appellant&rsquo;s insolvency and adjudication of insolvency were saved u/s.37(1), Provincial Insolvency Act, 1920 and that notwithstanding the annulment of insolvency against the appellant and his mother, the sale deed executed on 11.03.1983 was valid. Headnotes&dagger; Provincial Insolvency Act, 1920 &ndash; s.37 &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 25-09-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 12048/2018</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_9_1539_1558','2025INSC1159','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' on